The incident occurred near Ajmeri Garden, witnessed by the victim's mother. Police arrested Aqueel and seized the vehicle. Authorities stated a past dispute existed between the two men.
title: ‘Chicken' dispute turns fatal: Man run over by car in MP; mother witnesses horror

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: India is expediting the acquisition of Rafael's X Guard decoy system to bolster the Rafale fighter jets' missile defense capabilities, crucial for operations in contested airspace. The system, used by Israel, lures missiles away from the aircraft.
title: Decoy system for Rafale: India to speed up X-guard for IAF fighter jets

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The ministry of civil aviation has clarified that the Aircraft Accident Investigation Bureau's (AAIB) report on the Air India Flight 171 crash is preliminary. The investigation into the deadly crash of the Boeing 787-8 Dreamliner, which occurred shortly after takeoff from Ahmedabad and claimed the lives of 240 people, is still ongoing.
title: 'Don't jump to any conclusion': Centre reacts to AI 171 crash probe report

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A preliminary report on the Air India crash in Ahmedabad reveals a 2018 US report flagged a potential fuel control switch issue in Boeing aircraft. The FAA bulletin warned of possible disengagement of the switch locking feature, potentially causing unintended engine shutdowns. Inspections weren't mandatory, and the crash investigation continues, focusing on engine failure without pilot input.
title: 'Advisory, not mandatory': Did FAA flag fuel control switch issue on Boeing jets in 2018?

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: A preliminary report on the Air India Flight AI171 crash revealed a catastrophic engine failure just seconds after takeoff from Ahmedabad. Both engines of the Boeing 787-8 Dreamliner lost power due to a sudden fuel supply cutoff, leading to the fatal accident. Investigators are probing the cause, focusing on fuel control switches and a prior FAA warning.
title: Air India plane crash: What are the fuel control switches under scrutiny?

author: etimes.in
description: Ankita Lokhande shares her wellness routine. It includes 'magic water' and supplements. She consumes soaked methi seeds and dalchini water. Her morning also includes aloe vera and saffron water. Ankita dedicates time to prayer. She recites religious texts. She charges water near the temple. This water is consumed throughout the day.
title: Ankita Lokhande shares the secret behind her glowing skin: safron drink and more

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Bollywood's star kids often benefit from their family names. However, Hrithik Roshan has emerged as the wealthiest. His net worth surpasses other star kids like Sara Ali Khan and Aryan Khan. Roshan's success stems from hit films like 'Krrish' and 'War'. He also earns from endorsements and his HRX brand. He owns luxurious properties and cars.
title: Bollywood’s richest star kid: Rs 3130 crore fortune, luxury cars, sea-view home

author: AMARJEET SINGH
description: Sidhi BJP MP Rakesh Mishra's suggestion to admit pregnant women a week early to address the lack of roads in Khaddi Khurd village has sparked controversy. Influencer Leela Sahu highlighted the issue, emphasizing the difficulty ambulances face, especially during monsoon.
title: 'Delivery ke pehle uthwa lenge': BJP MP’s bizarre fix after pregnant woman demands road; sparks row

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Google has acquired top AI coding talent from Windsurf, including CEO Varun Mohan and co-founder Douglas Chen, for its DeepMind division in a $2.4 billion deal. This move comes after OpenAI's acquisition attempt failed due to Microsoft's IP access demands. Google gains non-exclusive licensing rights to Windsurf's AI coding technology, strengthening its position in the competitive AI-powered software development market.
title: Google recruits Windsurf CEO, after OpenAI's $3B deal falls apart

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Mohammed Siraj dedicated his wickets in the Lord's Test to footballer Diogo Jota, who tragically passed away in a car accident. Siraj, a Cristiano Ronaldo and Portugal fan, expressed his shock and sadness upon hearing the news. He emphasized the unpredictability of life and wanted to honor Jota with his on-field gesture, reflecting the shared emotions felt across different sports.
title: 'Life is very unpredictable': Siraj speaks about his Diogo Jota tribute - watch

author: TAMAGHNA BANERJEE
description: A management student in Kolkata is under arrest. Paramanand Toppaunwar allegedly raped a female acquaintance. The incident occurred at the boys hostel inside the institute campus. The survivor claims she was invited for a counselling session. She alleges she was given a drink and then assaulted. Police are investigating the security lapses at the institute.
title: ‘Spiked drink, pizza’: Another woman raped inside college premises; one arrested

description: Political tensions rise in Bihar as another businessman, Vikram Jha, is murdered in Patna. Tejashwi Yadav criticizes chief minister Nitish Kumar over rising crime. This incident follows the killings of Gopal Khemka and another sand mining businessman. The RJD accuses the government of lawlessness. The NDA counters, alleging the opposition seeks to revive "Jungleraaj".
title: Another businessman shot dead in Patna: Tejashwi slams Nitish; questions CM's silence

author: TNN
description: A judicial commission report has implicated the Karnataka State Cricket Association, Royal Challengers Bengaluru, and the police for security lapses contributing to the Bengaluru stampede that claimed 11 lives during IPL victory celebrations. The report, submitted to Chief Minister Siddaramaiah, highlights failures in crowd control, coordination, and the issuance of physical tickets without digital options.
title: Bengaluru stampede: Judicial panel blames RCB, police & KSCA; Siddaramaiah responds

author: TOI Education
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi distributed over 51,000 appointment letters to newly recruited government employees during the 16th edition of Rozgar Mela on July 12, 2025. Conducted across 47 locations, this event marks a significant milestone in the Rozgar Mela initiative, facilitating over 1 million appointments. Recruits will join various central government departments, strengthening public service and offering stable careers.
title: Rozgar Mela 2025: Over 51,000 jobs offered to youths in government posts

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Rajinikanth's 'Coolie' is creating buzz with its second single 'Monica,' composed by Anirudh Ravichander. The song features Pooja Hegde and Soubin Shahir, whose unexpected dance moves have stolen the spotlight. Directed by Lokesh Kanagaraj and featuring a star-studded cast, 'Coolie' is set for an August 14 release, clashing with 'War 2' at the box office.
title: 'Monica' song out: Pooja Hegde shines, Soubin Shahir steals the show

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Union Minister Chirag Paswan has reportedly received a death threat on social media, prompting a formal police complaint. The threat, allegedly made by an Instagram user, is being investigated by the Patna Cyber Police Station. Paswan recently announced his candidacy for the upcoming Bihar elections, where his party, LJP (Ram Vilas), is expected to continue its alliance with the NDA.
title: Bihar polls: Chirag Paswan gets death threat on social media; complaint filed

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A preliminary report on the Air India AI 171 crash reveals a sudden fuel cutoff to both engines moments after takeoff from Ahmedabad. The London-bound Boeing 787, carrying a heavy load, failed to gain altitude, clipping structures before crashing into a building.
title: Fuel switches found in ‘RUN’ position: Aftermath of AI 171 crash in images; what the wreckage shows

author: TNN
description: VHP has initiated a certification drive, pasting stickers on shops along Kanwar Yatra routes in Delhi, guaranteeing vegetarian food in accordance with 'sanatani' values. This action follows a proposal to close meat shops, though the MCD lacks the authority.
title: Kanwar Yatra: 'Sanatani' stickers on Delhi shops; VHP certifies vegetarian-only outlets

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Measles is resurging in the U.S., reaching a 33-year high due to lowered vaccination rates and misinformation. Beyond the initial symptoms, measles weakens the immune system, leading to increased vulnerability to other infections like pneumonia and ear infections. Severe complications such as SSPE, myocarditis, blindness, and pregnancy complications highlight the importance of vaccination to prevent long-term health consequences.
title: Measles isn’t over with rash, problems that can follow the infection

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Shanaya Kapoor's debut film, Aankhon Ki Gustaakhiyan, had a slow start at the box office, earning an estimated Rs 35 lakh on its opening day. Despite the modest numbers, Shanaya received strong support from family and Bollywood colleagues, including Arjun Kapoor and Karan Johar. Shanaya Kapoor called the delayed debut a blessing.
title: Aankhon Ki Gustaakhiyan: Shanaya Kapoor’s debut film opens with Rs 35 lakh

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Conservative influencers, who had banked on explosive revelations implicating elites, were incensed. Bondi’s office had built expectations with Phase 1 of the “Epstein Files” back in February—a series of binders handed out to right-wing media figures that mostly repackaged previously leaked information. With the July memo’s flat conclusions, fury erupted.
title: Epstein Files: Will Kash Patel resign? The story so far

author: TOI Education
description: The Gujarat Board (GSEB) has announced the Class 12 Science supplementary results today, July 12th, on gseb.org. Students who appeared for the Purak Pariksha in June can now check their scores online, via WhatsApp, or SMS. The provisional marksheets are available for download, with original certificates issued by schools. Passing requires 33% in each subject and overall.
title: GSEB HSC Result 2025: Gujarat class 12th science supplementary results declared

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Jasprit Bumrah avoided controversy regarding frequent ball changes during the third Test against England. Shubman Gill argued with umpires about replacement balls. Despite the issue, Bumrah delivered a strong performance, taking 5/74 including the wickets of Harry Brook and Joe Root. Bumrah also discussed his role in mentoring younger players, emphasising on personalised guidance.
title: IND vs ENG Test: 'I don't want to get my match fees deducted' Bumrah on ball change controversy

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: The United States is considering an interim trade agreement with India, potentially setting tariffs below 20%, a more favorable position than other regional nations. While many countries face tariff hikes, India may avoid a formal notice.
title: India-US trade deal: Trump administration may cut tariff to below 20% - check details

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Novak Djokovic's Wimbledon reign ended as Jannik Sinner defeated him in straight sets. The 38-year-old cited age and physical struggles, acknowledging their impact. Aiming for a record 25th Grand Slam, Djokovic's defeat marks his struggle with best-of-five matches. Despite the setback, he intends to return next year, emphasizing his dedication to Grand Slams.
title: 'Reality hits like never before': Djokovic addresses retirement; Sinner vs Alcaraz in Wimbledon final

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Rishabh Pant's finger injury during the third Test at Lord's raised concerns about his batting eligibility, but ICC rules permit him to bat at his usual position as the injury was legitimate. This contrasts with tactical absences, which could restrict batting order. Pant's return at No. 5 was a significant advantage for India, allowing him to contribute despite the pain.
title: Why Pant was allowed to bat at his regular spot despite missing fielding duty - Explained

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Taylor Swift and Blake Lively's friendship faces trouble. Sources say they are not in contact. This follows Lively's connection to Justin Baldoni's legal issues. Lively's image suffered, straining the bond. Swift is now focused on Travis Kelce. Lively seeks new high-profile connections. The friendship may be over. Both are moving on with their careers and relationships.
title: 'Friendship is done': Swift unlikely to forgive Blake Lively after betrayal

author: NIKHIL SHARMA
description: Radhika Yadav, a tennis player, was murdered by her father, Deepak Yadav. The reason was disagreement over her tennis academy. Deepak was upset by comments about Radhika's character. He shot her multiple times at their house in Sector 57. Police investigation revealed Deepak's psychological issues. He was produced in court and is in police remand.
title: ‘People questioned her character’: Father felt insulted — 15 days later, shot Radhika 4 times

author: TNN
description: A four-story building in northeast Delhi's Seelampur area collapsed on Saturday, leading to a frantic rescue operation. Several individuals are feared trapped under the debris of the ground-plus-three-floor structure. Fire officials have confirmed that three to four people have already been hospitalized, and seven fire tenders are at the scene working to save others.
title: Delhi: 4-storey building collapses in Seelampur; several trapped

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: A preliminary report on the Air India 171 crash in Ahmedabad, which killed 260, reveals a sequence of engine shutdowns moments after takeoff. Cockpit recordings indicate pilot confusion regarding the fuel cutoff, and a distress call was issued just before the crash. The investigation continues to analyze wreckage and components, with no immediate recommendations for Boeing 787 operators.
title: Engine 1 and Engine 2 cut off within 1 second: What caused Air India plane crash? 10 key findings

description: Ayesha Curry recently shared a heartwarming photo of her youngest child, Cai, sparking a frenzy online due to the striking resemblance to his father, Steph Curry. Some even noted a resemblance to Steph's mother, Sonya Curry, highlighting the Curry family's strong genes.
